Try cleaning the project
Also, v7 includes v4 so you don’t have to include both

Why don’t you upgrade v7 then?
once I update v7 to 22.x. there will be `requestFeature() must be called before adding content` and it crashes
I think then you should focus on fixing that instead of trying to force incompatible versions to work together. You’ll get wayyyyy more problems later down the line with that setup. :wink:
agree
Because if you exclude v4 from v7, it would probably be forced to use the newer version, which probably has tons of incompatibilities
ok, so your suggestion is to upgrade both v4 and v7 to the latest version?

In your gradle file, the only thing you’ll need is `compile 'com.android.support:appcompat-v7:22.2.0'`
don’t include v4 yourself
There’s a bug with the latest support library on that - <https://stackoverflow.com/questions/30526791/cannot-access-dialogstyle>
